article.headline: North Florida 57, Concordia, N.Y. 41
article.story: JACKSONVILLE, Fla. (AP) -- Chris Timberlake had 10 points to lead North Florida to a 57-41 win over Concordia, N.Y., on Friday night. Justin Cecil pulled down 10 rebounds and added eight points for North Florida (1-2). James Grimball scored nine points for North Florida while Tom Hammonds added eight. Alban Shala led Division II Concordia with 13 points, followed by Richard Fields, who added nine. Kenny Gaskins III had 11 rebounds for the Clippers (0-1) and scored seven points. Torrence McGill added eight points and nine rebounds. The Clippers went into the half trailing North Florida by three points, at 35-32. But Concordia scored just nine points after halftime and were outpaced by the Ospreys, who scored 22 in the second half.
